      "id": "RQ-0072",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Retry Mac CLI health timeouts before warning users",
      "description": "A single CLI health timeout immediately becomes an unavailable warning in operational health. Goal: self-heal transient health-check timeouts with bounded retries before surfacing a warning, and include attempt diagnostics only if the final health state remains unavailable.",
      "priority": "medium",
      "tags": [
        "scan",
        "macos",
        "health",
        "reliability"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/RalphCLIHealthChecker.swift",
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/Workspace+HealthAndCaching.swift",
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/WorkspaceOperationalHealth.swift",
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCoreTests/CLIHealthCheckerTests.swift",
        "make macos-test-contracts"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/RalphCLIHealthChecker.swift:74-99 starts exactly one health-check task per request; there is no retry loop around performHealthCheck.",
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/RalphCLIHealthChecker.swift:193-218 maps TimeoutError directly to CLIHealthStatus.unavailable(.timeout).",
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/WorkspaceOperationalHealth.swift:221-246 renders timeout as 'CLI health check timed out' with severity .warning.",
        "Command run: make agent-ci -> passed docs-only gate; no baseline CI blocker reproduced."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Add a small bounded retry/backoff policy for TimeoutError and transient process errors in CLIHealthChecker without retrying permanent missing/executable/permission failures.",
        "Track attempt count and last redacted diagnostic inside CLIHealthStatus or associated diagnostics for terminal timeout states.",
        "Keep operational health quiet or informational while retries are pending; show warning only after the final failed attempt.",
        "Add CLIHealthChecker tests for timeout-then-success, timeout-exhausted, and permanent no-retry failures.",
        "Verify by running CLIHealthCheckerTests or make macos-test-contracts, then make agent-ci."
      ],
      "notes": [],
      "request": "scan finding",
