    {
      "id": "RQ-0073",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Align Mac RetryConfiguration semantics with actual attempts",
      "description": "RetryConfiguration is named and documented as maxRetries, but RetryHelper interprets it as total attempts. This can lead maintainers to believe users get more self-healing attempts than they actually do. Goal: make the type/API documentation and tests unambiguous.",
      "priority": "low",
      "tags": [
        "scan",
        "macos",
        "typing",
        "retry"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/RetryHelper.swift",
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCoreTests/RetryHelperTests.swift",
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCoreTests/RetryIntegrationTests.swift",
        "make macos-test-contracts"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/RetryHelper.swift:26-41 defines public let maxRetries and comments 'Default configuration: 3 retries'.",
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/RetryHelper.swift:151-172 loops for attempt in 1...configuration.maxRetries and reports maxAttempts=configuration.maxRetries, so the value is total attempts, not retries after the first failure.",
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCoreTests/RetryHelperTests.swift:60-80 uses maxRetries: 3 and succeeds on the third total attempt, confirming current behavior.",
        "Command run: make agent-ci -> passed docs-only gate; no baseline CI blocker reproduced."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Choose one canonical semantic: rename/document the property as maxAttempts, or change implementation to perform initial attempt plus maxRetries retry attempts.",
        "Update comments, call sites, and tests so progress labels and attempt counts match the chosen semantic.",
        "If API compatibility requires retaining maxRetries, add an explicit deprecation/comment shim with a cleanup path.",
        "Verify by running RetryHelperTests/RetryIntegrationTests or make macos-test-contracts, then make agent-ci."
      ],
